```

## Installation Workflow

### Step 1: Read Deployment State

**Load VPS connection info:**
```bash
VPS_IP=$(jq -r '.vpsIp' deployment-state.json)
SSH_KEY_PATH={{security.sshKeyPath}}

echo "📍 Connecting to VPS: $VPS_IP"
```

### Step 2: Connect to VPS via SSH

**Establish SSH connection:**
```bash
ssh -i $SSH_KEY_PATH root@$VPS_IP
```

### Step 3: Install Docker

**Run Docker installation script:**
```bash
# Update system
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get upgrade -y

# Install Docker
curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com -o get-docker.sh
sudo sh get-docker.sh

# Enable Docker
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo systemctl start docker

# Verify
docker --version
docker compose version
```

**Expected Output:**
```
Docker version 24.0.7, build afdd53b
Docker Compose version v2.23.0
```

### Step 4: Install Appwrite

**Run Appwrite installer:**
```bash
cd /root
docker run -it --rm \
    --volume /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \
    --volume "$(pwd)"/appwrite:/usr/src/code/appwrite:rw \
    --entrypoint="install" \
    appwrite/appwrite:{{appwrite.version}}
```

**Interactive prompts (automated responses):**
```
Choose your server HTTP port: 80
Choose your server HTTPS port: 443
Choose a secret API key: (auto-generated)
Enter your Appwrite hostname: {{domain.appwriteSubdomain}}.{{domain.rootDomain}}
Enter a DNS A record hostname: {{domain.appwriteSubdomain}}.{{domain.rootDomain}}
```

**Automated installation script:**
```bash
cd /root/appwrite

# Generate secure keys
export APPWRITE_SECRET=$(openssl rand -hex 32)
export DB_PASSWORD=$(openssl rand -base64 32)

# Update .env with our configuration
cat > .env <<EOF
_APP_OPENSSL_KEY_V1=$APPWRITE_SECRET
_APP_DOMAIN={{domain.appwriteSubdomain}}.{{domain.rootDomain}}
_APP_DOMAIN_TARGET={{domain.appwriteSubdomain}}.{{domain.rootDomain}}
_APP_DB_PASS=$DB_PASSWORD
_APP_OPTIONS_FORCE_HTTPS={{#if security.enableSSL}}enabled{{else}}disabled{{/if}}
_APP_CONSOLE_EMAIL={{appwrite.adminEmail}}
_APP_CONSOLE_PASSWORD={{appwrite.adminPassword}}
{{#if appwrite.features.enableFunctions}}
_APP_FUNCTIONS_SIZE_LIMIT=30000000
{{/if}}
{{#if appwrite.features.enableMessaging}}
_APP_SMS_PROVIDER={{appwrite.messaging.provider}}
{{/if}}
{{#if appwrite.features.enableStorage}}
_APP_STORAGE_LIMIT={{appwrite.storage.limit}}
{{/if}}
EOF
```

### Step 5: Start Appwrite Stack

**Launch all containers:**
```bash
cd /root/appwrite
docker compose up -d
```

**Monitor startup:**
```bash
# Watch container startup
docker compose ps

# View logs
docker compose logs -f
```

**Expected containers (17 total):**
```
appwrite           # Main API server
appwrite-realtime  # WebSocket server
appwrite-worker-*  # Background workers (9 workers)
mariadb            # Database
redis              # Cache
telegraf           # Metrics collector
influxdb           # Time-series database
traefik            # Reverse proxy
```

### Step 6: Health Check Validation

**Wait for all services to be healthy:**
```bash
echo "⏳ Waiting for Appwrite to be healthy..."

until curl -f -s http://localhost/health > /dev/null 2>&1; do
    echo "  Waiting for health endpoint..."
    sleep 5
done

echo "✅ Appwrite is healthy!"
```

**Verify all containers running:**
```bash
CONTAINERS=$(docker compose ps --format json | jq -r 'select(.State == "running") | .Name' | wc -l)

if [ "$CONTAINERS" -eq 17 ]; then
    echo "✅ All 17 containers running"
else
    echo "⚠️ Only $CONTAINERS/17 containers running"
    docker compose ps
    exit 1
fi
```

**Test health endpoint:**
```bash
curl -s http://localhost/health | jq '.'
```

**Expected response:**
```json
{
  "status": "pass",
  "ping": "pong",
  "version": "{{appwrite.version}}",
  "services": {
    "database": "pass",
    "cache": "pass",
    "queue": "pass",
    "storage": "pass"
  }
}
```

